aaflib
------------------------------------------
The aaflib is an implementation of the mathematical construct of affine
arithmetics in C++. This construct has been introduced by Stolfi et. al. Their
c-library can be found at
http://www.ic.unicamp.br/~stolfi/EXPORT/software/c/Index.html#libaa. The aaflib
is based on the libaffa, a reimplemention of the original library, but has been
developed further. It has been used as main calculation library for a
spice-like nonlinear circuit simulator. Currently the library and the simulator
are developed at the Institute of Microelectronic Systems in Hannover, Germany.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libaaf-devel-0.1-1bl1
  libaaf0-0.1-1bl1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/foolnotion/aaflib

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/foolnotion/aaflib/archive/v0.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack aaflib-0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./aaflib-0.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/aaflib-0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/aaflib-0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libaaf0-0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libaaf-devel-0.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(aaflib)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/aaflib.README

(libaaf0)
  /usr/bin/cygaaf-0.dll

(libaaf-devel)
  /usr/include/aa.h
  /usr/include/aa_aaf.h
  /usr/include/aa_exceptions.h
  /usr/include/aa_interval.h
  /usr/include/aa_rounding.h
  /usr/lib/libaaf.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/aaflib.pc

